{"id":"feedreader-8e0","title":"Pre-group feeds by category to fix O(N×M) template performance regression","description":"The folder-tree template in base.html iterates all 200 feeds for each of 25 categories (O(feeds×categories) = 5,000 reflect-based iterations) to match feeds to folders. This is the dominant cost in page renders — 85% of CPU in profiling — and has pushed / and /category/{id} median response times from ~23ms to ~52ms, consistently failing the 50ms perf threshold.

Fix: build a map[int64][]Feed (categoryID → feeds) in getCommonData() Go code and pass it as FeedsByCategory in template data. Change the folder-tree template to range over (index $root.FeedsByCategory $catID) instead of filtering all feeds per category. This reduces the hot loop from O(feeds×categories) to O(feeds) — a ~25x reduction in reflect.Value.call overhead.

Secondary: consider whether the ETag SHA-256 buffering and the growing getCommonData query set (queue counts, alert counts, user settings) warrant further optimization, but the template loop is the primary bottleneck.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"exedev@lynx-fairy.exe.xyz","created_at":"2026-03-03T00:39:23Z","created_by":"exe.dev user","updated_at":"2026-03-03T00:39:23Z"}

